<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n44153d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n44" href="#n44153d">N44 (VI.B.34)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n44all.htm#n44153d"> 153(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Alba of Ravens</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In fact, according to an inveterate tradition, it was violation of the law of copyright <font color="green">[in the Psalter of St. Jerome brought from Rome by St. Finnian]</font> that led to <font color="green">[Columcille&apos;s]</font> exile. &hellip; Whatever be the truth of the matter, some crisis occurred, when he was at the height of his success, to induce him to leave the land he loved. &hellip; in the company of twelve others (the Irish, as a rule, conformed to the Apostolic pattern) he directed his course to &ldquo;Alba of the ravens&rdquo;. <small> F.J. Sheed, ed. <a name="FJSI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FJSI"><cite title="source">The Irish Way</cite></a> (May 1932) [<font size="-1">ST. COLUMCILLE</font> (521-597)] 51</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
